meanings.sent1: The outwrestled wrestler looked disappointed after the match.
meanings.sent2: The outwrestled team showed good sportsmanship despite losing.
meanings.sent3: The outwrestled wrestler joked, 'I guess I need more practice!'
meanings.sent4: The outwrestled team felt like they were no match for their opponents.
meanings.sent5: The outwrestled wrestler's defeat was evident in their body language.

meanings.definition: To have wrestled better than someone else.
meanings.sent1: He outwrestled his opponent with skillful moves.
meanings.sent2: She outwrestled her rival to win the championship.
meanings.sent3: The cat outwrestled the dog for the last piece of food.
meanings.sent4: The outwrestled wrestler's victory was a testament to their hard work.
meanings.sent5: The outwrestled team celebrated their well-deserved win.
